RenAmp is a personal software project developed by Claudio Cataldo.

This repository is publicly available for portfolio, educational, and evaluation purposes. The source code demonstrates real-time audio programming techniques, DSP architecture, neural amplifier modeling integration, and modern C++ development practices.

